name: Has Jay Slater been found
summary: A comprehensive search for Jay Slater, a missing British teen in Tenerife, has intensified, with police expanding their efforts and the public's support growing. The missing teen's mother has expressed confidence in the enhanced search, while his employer has defended his character against negative media portrayals. Law enforcement has focused their search on a village and valley where Slater's phone was detected, prompting a thorough investigation of surrounding buildings. Despite efforts, a firefighter has voiced concerns about the unusual nature of Slater's disappearance. name: Suranne Jones
summary: Across various news outlets, there is widespread coverage of a new documentary series titled "Suranne Jones: Investigating Witch Trials." This series, featuring actress Suranne Jones, explores the infamous Pendle witch trials, highlighting the misogyny and injustices that led to the mass executions of women in Lancashire. The documentary sheds light on the societal beliefs and fears that fueled these trials, and Jones delves into the historical records and conducts experiments to gain a deeper understanding of the experiences of those accused. One review emphasizes the emotional impact of the series, stating that the misogyny portrayed may incite anger and frustration. The series also offers insights into Jones's personal experiences and motivations for investigating this dark chapter in history.
